obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (100123)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100123&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Carriage of Goods by Sea`
  line `Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 10th day of September, 2025, vide notification No. S.O. 4082 (E), dated 8th day of September, 2025, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (100124)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100124&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "applicable rules" mean the applicable rules provided in the Schedule to this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notify" with its grammatical variation and cognate expressions shall be construed accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) "Schedule" means the Schedule annexed to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (100125)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100125&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the applicable rules laid down`
  line `in the Schedule shall have effect in relation to and in connection with the carriage of goods by sea in`
  line `ships carrying goods from any port in India to any other port, whether in or outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (100126)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `No implied absolute undertaking in contracts to which applicable rules apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100126&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `There shall`
  line `be no implied absolute undertaking in any contract for the carriage of goods by sea, to which the`
  line `applicable rules apply, by the carrier of the goods to provide a seaworthy ship.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (100127)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Statement as to application of Schedule to be included in bills of lading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100127&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every bill of lading,`
  line `or similar document of title, issued in India, which contains or is evidence of any contract to which the`
  line `applicable rules apply, shall contain an express statement that it is to have effect subject to the applicable`
  line `rules laid down in the Schedule, as applied by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (100152)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Modification of Article VI of applicable rules in relation to goods carried in sailing ships and by specified routes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100152&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Article VI of the applicable rules shall, in relation to---`
  line
  line `(a) the carriage of goods by sea in sailing ships, carrying goods from any port in India to any`
  line `other port whether in or outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) the carriage of goods by sea in ships, carrying goods from a port in India notified in this`
  line `behalf, to a port in Sri Lanka specified in the said notification,`
  line
  line `have effect as though the said Article referred to goods of any class instead of to particular goods and`
  line `as though the proviso to the second paragraph of the said Article were omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (100129)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Modification of paragraphs 4 and 5 of Article III in relation to bulk cargoes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100129&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Where under`
  line `the custom of any trade,–---`
  line
  line `(a) the weight of any bulk cargo inserted in the bill of lading is a weight ascertained or accepted`
  line `by a third party other than the carrier or the shipper; and`
  line
  line `(b) the fact that the weight is so ascertained or accepted is stated in the bill of lading,`
  line
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in the applicable rules, the bill of lading shall not be deemed`
  line `to be prima facie evidence against the carrier of the receipt of goods of the weight so inserted in the bill`
  line `of lading, and the accuracy thereof at the time of shipment shall not be deemed to have been guaranteed`
  line `by the shipper.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (100130)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100130&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions, as it may deem necessary, for carrying out all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (100131)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Central Government to amend directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100131&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied`
  line `that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by notification, amend the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amendment notified under sub-section (1) shall have effect as if enacted in this Act and shall`
  line `come into force on the date of the notification, unless the notification otherwise directs.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (100132)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Laying of notification before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100132&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every notification issued under this Act shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a`
  line `total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions,`
  line `and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification or both Houses agree that`
  line `the notification should not be made, the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall`
  line `be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done in pursuance of that notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (100133)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100133&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years,`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (100134)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140&sectionId=100134&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_198_0_00005_2025-19_1757570478140
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Indian Carriage of Goods by Sea Act, 1925 (26 of 1925) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the repeal of the Act referred to in sub-section (1), it shall not affect,---`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the Act so repealed or anything done or any action taken or purported`
  line `to have been done or taken or suffered thereunder under the Act so repealed; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the Act so`
  line `repealed; or`
  line
  line `(c) the operation of any rule, notification, order, notice or direction issued or exemption granted`
  line `thereunder, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, and shall be in force until`
  line `it is repealed or superseded under the corresponding provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) any proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation, liability, penalty`
  line `as aforesaid, and any such proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any`
  line `such penalty may be imposed as if that Act had not been repealed; or`
  line
  line `(e) the reference made to the repealed Act under any other legislation, rule, order, or any other`
  line `legal instrument and any such reference shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions`
  line `of this Act, be construed to as a reference to this Act or its corresponding provisions.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this Act shall affect the operation of section 331 and the provisions of Part XA, of`
  line `the Merchant Shipping Act, 1958 (44 of 1958), or the operation of any other enactment for the time`
  line `being in force limiting the liability of the owners of sea-going vessels.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the provisions of section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply with regard to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
